Daily security audit of the ClaudeOS setup at ~/theborg.

Run the /security-review skill against the current state of ~/theborg. Specifically review:
- .claude/settings*.json files in each agent's workspace
- hooks configured in those settings
- exposed paths and permission rules
- Telegram access lists at ~/.claude/channels/telegram-*/access.json
- any new MCP servers added since last audit

Always email the result by piping it into `${BORG_ROOT}/.bin/notify-email.sh c4po` (reads the message from stdin and emails it to the user) — even when the audit is clean, so the user can confirm the job ran. Header: `Borg security audit — {YYYY-MM-DD} — {N} finding(s)`.
- If anything critical is found (auth weakness, dangerous permission, broken access policy, suspicious MCP server, leaked secret), include each finding and a recommended fix.
- If clean, the body is a one-liner: `All clear — no findings.`
